From d96dc13f3f48421229b617ff937d6e6e645b2e69 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?=C3=98yvind=20Harboe?= <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 33/34] fix: mock-cpu io.tcl source util.tcl via env var for
 Bazel sandbox
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The io.tcl used hardcoded relative paths to source util.tcl, guarded by
file exists checks. In the Bazel sandbox neither path resolves, so
util.tcl is silently skipped and match_pins is never defined, causing
floorplan to crash with "invalid command name match_pins".

Use $::env(SDC_FILE_EXTRA) which already points to util.tcl's sandbox
path (added in the SDC fix). This is the same pattern used for
constraint.sdc.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Øyvind Harboe <oyvind.harboe@zylin.com>
---
 flow/designs/asap7/mock-cpu/io.tcl | 8 +-------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/flow/designs/asap7/mock-cpu/io.tcl b/flow/designs/asap7/mock-cpu/io.tcl
index ea8b842fc..5591aab16 100644
--- a/flow/designs/asap7/mock-cpu/io.tcl
+++ b/flow/designs/asap7/mock-cpu/io.tcl
@@ -1,10 +1,4 @@
-# bazel has root of OpenROAD-flow-scripts as working directory
-foreach prefix {"" flow/} {
-  set f ${prefix}designs/src/mock-array/util.tcl
-  if { [file exists $f] } {
-    source $f
-  }
-}
+source $::env(SDC_FILE_EXTRA)
 
 set_io_pin_constraint -order -group -region bottom:* \
   -pin_names [concat [match_pins .*] [match_pins clk input 1]]
-- 
